Police in Embu on Monday arrested a taxi driver ferrying Sh2 million bhang packed in sacks.The Itabua police station officers were on patrol when they arrested Moses Kinyua on Karurina-Majimbo road in Embu West subcounty.The bhang was packed in stones and rolls. Kinyua said he had been hired by a customer to transport the sacks and bags from Chuka and he did not know it was bhang until he was arrested and detained by the police.The bhang was in the boot and the passenger seats.The bhang was packed in four sacks and polythene bags. It was being transported from Chuka in Tharka Nithi county to Muraru market in Mbeere South subcounty.Police said they are interrogating Kinyua to net more accomplices.